 I can use the compile-time JDK API instead of the artifact, and it looks like there's no coverage for that. Perhaps I could keep the testing Java only and avoid skipping native altogether. Yet, I’m also pondering the limitations with the public API and reflection. It seems that calling `DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance()` might engage the JDK’s SecuritySupport. I wonder if using `ServiceLoader` would be viable, but I'm hesitant about that too.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0266ed53936078e50169f540ce91f0819c9253e935addc8110\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9UDfKPjjeBHs-nLg7ZGxtAJCtd-9nfVJreGukrRCYlprEDjehBFs5fsrMZqARyu-nqG9PfBuNKXHZiqyGpdurbTHmhbpHiMbNxhMoVuJbyOk3U7QaPcDUvzWKoIbwu-UTuZkkEd9FVtlo73ezui5lgq9Xc6pLDJjESD6NMx7S9tyMvYpfZ1VXxD4lwcF6yIGJ5KbQ2G0FBhyo6TWP0lr9FQwxiJWFue3MGdheY_wbXnBEIzcTnvk7vhOh2WvbfD-V6Ih7wqsgNIGJfV21Qa747_shS8O0Wx6vb-b9UsUq1uHQWVWgUq0WRTZeaAF0bi_BcOdOOJxZhUTB3YgVMrNUKrKIFrkR4MCNFCKL1VAlPQCSycEc8ghmaZjM6Q9EexTRDpacOemiKk7nxnZHrNHLTXUXsQLYhvSnuih6ml1zShaWsHUF_tTgovBGnBsFMr4LwkOEmIbMOmGhBL5ug_6tTufpcRuVzpPCg6yTSjh4p_42N5l4oi7yd_LVR-oXR8wIWHbgjEGGgmldScHF3ZJ5hRZK8WmA43p-SZWJG8IwxZzCcrlQVbo6m0nuitNJwTyPxD6-loU1mptDO4irxuZJ02hhuO7484saEQUK16PSVRtAyMDIZJeUJWTCyWWAia36ouMm1W4PQ7Aut5u7zRH50suYIseUpHpvY8SJUsPx9QJTqs_zHPGPE5acIgnbMsDlqmPRYu2-bes3UNMQrQZmUOandlJC0J8-x5Gnuf3R2EZNmCpix4y8bnNO7KEnnUIvFrwxnMP9cmGins0UVS6_z_sQMFixA8wUe_nqTe8k3WqL26AnoTkGVQd5DRVZOQnpMPsRk3J9YkZ6W8ww6Bp9Y2Ik149xt6LVYGzThOks56DVVxeA4nX14d7Mh163mGLabVC5AqaLMm59fPEhj-SlJ3rLbgPmkYlsB92Gk24Wc7WEJ2LbOyrrt0M9QeRCYuZ56mGX6cOaiJ-slCpg7giOp8lBUbbk_7MHf6b4T9xhSJX-VTCEN0zaZm09AMIe2d7GbrWia-xBFBMfK_BoTerWmW_h7opF4cw98zaX6Fh0t9qmdHLKRXjYMkZ821RoU-5gNTm9kWDn2M16NS-eug2SS85T3ciUcTYOiD70P0Kg0a2kgeQUIjKlxfYD2tF14Xas8iAucFP0RnV2grHWOkKEsjKn2y2i0w5DgjO0TdynAmLNuy4aGiPut5BXsCglOZr51LQ6_wRmypa2iMFAi6BSWRBX145oyHPtAw5oNiep98lpgYlNQTnGp_N1G5XMAHbH8voC7kCn2mReG1KhdHC-SOuVJuqgeVLg2rLlIct2wSkwi3vDsbDKxy8yD5FkqJOdwD-TkKNO7VvJ6Y_W6grzwW0uTmaDF82M3TZAJzgkCKEpj-UjPYIYn1x7BIn