ad. But if the artifact was loaded at build, how can I ensure coverage while forcing an UnsupportedFeatureError in native?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Java API Options**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I can use the compile-time JDK API instead of the artifact, and it looks like there's no coverage for that. Perhaps I could keep the testing Java only and avoid skipping native altogether. Yet, I’m also pondering the limitations with the public API and reflection. It seems that calling `DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance()` might engage the JDK’s SecuritySupport. I wonder if using `ServiceLoader` would be viable, but I'm hesitant about that too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_iwp4n6ydehG2BoFwrF4k3nvE|fc_0266ed53936078e50169f540df2e80819ca9931b19aa55f02d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/build/native -path '*reflect*config*' -type f -print -exec grep -H \"SecuritySupport\" {} \\; | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5331, "output": 1187, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38774, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777680589128, "responseId": "resp_0266ed53936078e50169f540cdb320819ca1e64017676a89c4"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_iwp4n6ydehG2BoFwrF4k3nvE|fc_0266ed53936078e50169f540df2e80819ca9931b19aa55f02d", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "(no output)"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777680607588}]}
