e` | [dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py) | Coverage-driven loop using the dynamic-access report; targets uncovered call sites. |\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/architecture.md:201:| `optimistic_dynamic_access` | [optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py) | Variant of dynamic-access that primes coverage from source analysis. |\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/architecture.md:238:| `dynamic_access_report` | Parse `dynamic-access-coverage.json`, compute deltas, format prompts. |\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/architecture.md:270:  recovery, dynamic-access iteration, javac/java-run failure prompts).\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:21:2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:33:   dynamic-access coverage of already-supported libraries.\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:53:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:76:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:77:  strategies; see [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md).\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:89:  `dynamic-access-iteration`).\n../../forge_worktrees/2719-7a28ca2d/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:138:- [Dynamic access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) — guided test\n../../forge_worktrees/2719